THAT FEELS NORMAL.

00:38:06.951 --> 00:38:09.950
THE LOVE OF THIS RACE, FOR ME,
IS SUNRISE, SUNSET.

00:38:09.951 --> 00:38:16.950
JUST BLOWS MY MIND.
WHEN THE SUN DROPS AND DARKNESS

00:38:16.951 --> 00:38:22.950
FALLS, THE CIRCUIT COMES ALIVE.

00:38:22.951 --> 00:38:26.950
IT BECOMES QUICKER.
THE WIND DROPS.

00:38:26.951 --> 00:38:27.950
THE CARS ARE A BIT EASIER TO
DRIVE.

00:38:27.951 --> 00:38:30.950
BUT YOU HAVE TO GET USED TO
THAT CHANGE IN LIGHT, WHICH IS

00:38:30.951 --> 00:38:35.950
ALSO VERY DIFFICULT.
AND I DON'T KNOW IF YOU HAVE

00:38:35.951 --> 00:38:38.950
NOTICED, THERE IS A LOT OF BUGS
HERE AT THE MOMENT.

00:38:38.951 --> 00:38:39.950
YEAH -- HANNAH:
I SAW ONE EARLIER. [LAUGHTER]

00:38:39.951 --> 00:38:41.950
JENSON:
AFTER TWO LAPS YOU HAVE A

00:38:41.951 --> 00:38:43.950
COVERED WINDSCREEN, AND TRYING
